Business Brief -- Storage Technology Corp.:
   Distributor Offers to Buy
   Stock of Edata Scandinavia
Under its tender offer, Storage said it will pay 182
kroner ($30.88) in cash for each series A share and 170
kroner in cash for each B share.
   Storage, a maker and distributor of storage and retrieval
subsystems for computers, said it has had "a strong working
relationship for the last 10 years" with Edata, a distributor
of systems that store and manage large volumes of data.
   Storage, which had 1991 revenue of $1.58 billion, said
Edata's revenue for 1990 was $68.3 million, about 75% of
which was derived from the distribution of Storage products.